
// This code constructs a URL by concatenating various components using the [strings.concat] slot. It retrieves the request scheme and host, appends a static path "/assets/images/", and adds the file name from the [.arguments] node. The resulting URL is then assigned to the [.url] node using the [set-value] slot.
set-value:x:@.url
   strings.concat
      request.scheme
      .:"://"
      request.host
      .:/assets/images/
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/file/*/name
